'''Miyayama Site''' ({{ill|Miyayama Site|ja|宮山遺跡}}) is a {{ill|composite archaeological site|ja|複合遺跡}} located in Kamisaijo, Yahata-cho, Kakogawa City, Hyogo Prefecture. The site encompasses settlements from the {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代}} to the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代}}, as well as the {{ill|Miyayama Kofun Group|ja|宮山古墳群}} from the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代}}. It has been designated as a cultural property by Kakogawa City.
== Overview == [[File:Miyayama Otsuka Kofun, funkyu.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Miyayama Otsuka Kofun}}]] The central feature of the site is the {{ill|Hotategai-gata Kofun|ja|帆立貝形古墳}} called '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''', with a posterior diameter of 40 meters. Surrounding it are five smaller circular tumuli (diameters 15–20 meters) to the north and one to the south. On the eastern side, remains of a Jomon-period settlement, including a {{ill|paved stone structure|ja|敷石建物}}, have been discovered. The western side has been developed as the '''Miyayama Rural Park''', with observation areas and walking trails.
== Major Features == * '''Paved Stone Building''' – Late {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代}} * '''Ritual Site''' – {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代}} * '''Settlement Transition''' – From the Yayoi to the Heian period * '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''' – Middle Kofun period (5th century), {{ill|Keyhole-shaped burial mound|ja|前方後円墳}}, with a posterior diameter of 40 meters and height of 6 meters, and a 6-meter-wide surrounding moat. * '''Mound 1''' – Circular tumulus with a {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室}} (stone chamber), diameter of 20 meters, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 2''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 3''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 4''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 5''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 6''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period
<gallery> File:Miyayama jyomonjukyo1024.jpg|Remains of a Jomon-period structure File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-1, funkyu.jpg|Mound 1 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-1, sekishitsu.jpg|Stone chamber of Mound 1 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-2, funkyu.jpg|Mound 2 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-3, funkyu.jpg|Mound 3 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-4, funkyu.jpg|Mound 4 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-5, funkyu.jpg|Mound 5 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-6, funkyu.jpg|Mound 6 </gallery>
== Miyayama Rural Park == This park was developed under the national {{ill|Comprehensive Rural Development Model Project|ja|農村総合整備モデル事業}}. It features walking paths weaving between the mounds and a plaza area west of Miyayama Otsuka Kofun. The total area is 2,655.91 square meters.
