== Overview == [[File:Miyayama Otsuka Kofun, funkyu.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Miyayama Otsuka Kofun}}]] The central feature of the site is the {{ill|Hotategai-gata Kofun|ja|帆立貝形古墳}} called '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''', with a posterior diameter of 40 meters. Surrounding it are five smaller circular tumuli (diameters 15–20 meters) to the north and one to the south. On the eastern side, remains of a Jomon-period settlement, including a {{ill|paved stone structure|ja|敷石建物}}, have been discovered. The western side has been developed as the '''Miyayama Rural Park''', with observation areas and walking trails.
== Major Features == * '''Paved Stone Building''' – Late {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代}} * '''Ritual Site''' – {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代}} * '''Settlement Transition''' – From the Yayoi to the Heian period * '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''' – Middle Kofun period (5th century), {{ill|Keyhole-shaped burial mound|ja|前方後円墳}}, with a posterior diameter of 40 meters and height of 6 meters, and a 6-meter-wide surrounding moat. * '''Mound 1''' – Circular tumulus with a {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber}} (stone chamber), diameter of 20 meters, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 2''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 3''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 4''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 5''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 6''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period
