== Major Features == * '''Paved Stone Building''' – Late {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jomon period|qq=}} * '''Ritual Site''' – {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yayoi period|qq=}} * '''Settlement Transition''' – From the Yayoi to the Heian period * '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''' – Middle Kofun period (5th century), {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}}, with a posterior diameter of 40 meters and height of 6 meters, and a 6-meter-wide surrounding moat. * '''Mound 1''' – Circular tumulus with a {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|13=User:Immanuelle/Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}} (stone chamber), diameter of 20 meters, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 2''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 3''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 4''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 5''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 6''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period
