[[File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa), gaikan.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Overview of the Miyayama Kofun Group (Mound 1 at the center)}}]] {{Location map|Japan Hyōgo Prefecture| label = Miyayama Site| position = bottom| mark = Red pog.svg| marksize = 10|relief = 1| width = 250| caption={{Left|Location map.}}}}
'''Miyayama Site''' ({{ill|Miyayama Site|ja|宮山遺跡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyayama Site|qq=}}) is a {{ill|composite archaeological site|ja|複合遺跡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/composite archaeological site|qq=}} located in Kamisaijo, Yahata-cho, Kakogawa City, Hyōgo Prefecture. The site encompasses settlements from the {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jomon period|qq=}} to the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heian period|qq=}}, as well as the {{ill|Miyayama Kofun Group|ja|宮山古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyayama Kofun Group|qq=}} from the {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun period|qq=}}. It has been designated as a cultural property by Kakogawa City.
== Overview == [[File:Miyayama Otsuka Kofun, funkyu.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Miyayama Otsuka Kofun}}]] The central feature of the site is the {{ill|Hotategai-gata Kofun|ja|帆立貝形古墳|1=Scallop Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hotategai-gata Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Scallop Kofun|qq=}} called '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''', with a posterior diameter of 40 meters. Surrounding it are five smaller circular tumuli (diameters 15–20 meters) to the north and one to the south. On the eastern side, remains of a Jomon-period settlement, including a {{ill|paved stone structure|ja|敷石建物|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/paved stone structure|qq=}}, have been discovered. The western side has been developed as the '''Miyayama Rural Park''', with observation areas and walking trails.
== Major Features == * '''Paved Stone Building''' – Late {{ill|Jomon period|ja|縄文時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jomon period|qq=}} * '''Ritual Site''' – {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yayoi period|qq=}} * '''Settlement Transition''' – From the Yayoi to the Heian period * '''Miyayama Otsuka Kofun''' – Middle Kofun period (5th century), {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}}, with a posterior diameter of 40 meters and height of 6 meters, and a 6-meter-wide surrounding moat. * '''Mound 1''' – Circular tumulus with a {{ill|Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokoana-shiki sekishitsu|13=User:Immanuelle/Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=}} (stone chamber), diameter of 20 meters, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 2''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 3''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 4''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 5''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period * '''Mound 6''' – Circular tumulus with a stone chamber, Late Kofun period
<gallery> File:Miyayama jyomonjukyo1024.jpg|Remains of a Jomon-period structure File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-1, funkyu.jpg|Mound 1 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-1, sekishitsu.jpg|Stone chamber of Mound 1 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-2, funkyu.jpg|Mound 2 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-3, funkyu.jpg|Mound 3 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-4, funkyu.jpg|Mound 4 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-5, funkyu.jpg|Mound 5 File:Miyayama Kofun Group (Kakogawa)-6, funkyu.jpg|Mound 6 </gallery>
== Miyayama Rural Park == This park was developed under the national {{ill|Comprehensive Rural Development Model Project|ja|農村総合整備モデル事業|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Comprehensive Rural Development Model Project|qq=}}. It features walking paths weaving between the mounds and a plaza area west of Miyayama Otsuka Kofun. The total area is 2,655.91 square meters.
== Cultural Properties == === Kakogawa City Designated Cultural Properties === * '''Historic Site''' ''' Miyayama Site – Designated on April 1, 1968<ref>[https://www.city.kakogawa.lg.jp/soshikikarasagasu/kyouiku/kakuka/kyoikushidobu/bunkazai_cyosa/bunkazai/1489194630431.html List of Designated Cultural Properties] (Kakogawa City Board of Education).</ref>.
== Visitor Information == '''Address''' 675-1204, Kamisaijo, Yahata-cho, Kakogawa City, Hyōgo Prefecture
